snippet.textDisplay: I was very sad when I learnt that Uber would be merging with Grab. I’ve had nothing but positive experiences with Uber drivers. But there were so many times when I booked a ride through Grab, and then have the drivers be super creepy. One time, this guy called my number to confirm my location... Then during the ride, he started hitting on me. I told him I was happily married. He said, “Married cannot have friends?”. Please lah. I’m not naive. You were hitting on me. I know your intentions aren’t pure. And then after the ride ended, he texted me on Whatsapp! What happened to user privacy?? I thought Grab was supposed to mask numbers. :( Another time this other Grab driver told me he was married but his wife allowed him to have girlfriends. I was like, “that’s cool, bro. I’m strictly monogamous with my husband.” It is terrifying to be stuck in an enclosed vehicle with someone whom is trying to hit on you. :(

snippet.textDisplay: It’s not about the timing, it’s about the demand. Uber uses an area effect surge so the price seems more fair to everyone using in that area. Grab surge is more specific so a certain amount of people will be charged at high surge and the rest around the area might not even have surge. I prefer uber surge system it’s more fair to both drivers and passengers.

snippet.textDisplay:
I always take grab and uber and I always ask the Uncle what is the weirdest passenger they have met, below is my top 3 complied list.

1. Pretty lady taking a ride to west coast, upon arriving at location, she claims she has no money and starts stripping (including her undergarments). Driver thought it was “haram” so he gave her his number for her to contact him for payment in the future. In the end, she did contact him but for sexual favours.

2. Driver had a hard time finding the passenger. So he calls her and realise it was a girl lying on the floor, looking at the sky. When she boarded the car, she was fully wet. (It was not raining and it was broad daylight) and later asked if she could smoke in the car. I asked the driver if she was drunk, but he said no. Neither did he dare to engage in a conversation with her.

3. Driver picked up a person from IMH and the payment mode was cash. When the person alighted, driver did not dare to ask for payment because he was afraid the person was mentally unsound.


If these are not enough, here’s my personal experience.
My Boyfriend and I took a share ride and when We boarded, there was a Chinese National couple. The female mentioned she was going to meet 洪俊扬 and is nervous about it. on the car ride, she plays her ukelele and was singing. As it was quite tight (small car/ukelele takes up space), I told my Boyfriend who was sitting infront to help me let her know not to play the ukelele in the car. My boyfriend told her to stop playing and she was shocked. She asked her Boyfriend what my Boyfriend meant. She did indeed stop playing the ukelele. But then she started to sing her self-composed songs in the car. #facepalm #worseexperience

snippet.textDisplay: If you're going to the airport, DON'T GRABSHARE IF YOU'RE BRINGING YOUR WHOLE CLOSET (or if you have a lot of stuff with you in general). Just be considerate and book your own ride... Other passengers might need the space too! There was once when I had to place my luggage on my lap because the other rider brought so much along with them and wanted to save a few dollars by sharing the ride...
